BOTTOM LINE UP FRONT (BLUF)

Stocks: AAPL, MSFT, JPM, V, JNJ, PFE, WMT, NKE, XOM, VZ, T, NEE The categories are: Best Bang per Buck: These are low risk, high reward, stable stocks with high returns, and are predictable for long term investment. High Performers: Perform Very Well, ideal also for long term investments. High Risk-Reward: Prone to drastic rises and falls, might be suitable for day traders, and short options trading. Average Performers: Not much to write home about, decent for portfolio diversity Below Average Performers: Perform below the 30 day U.S Treasure Bond, not worth the risk, buy bonds instead. Disaster-Avoid: Steady losses on average, might be worth shorting as it is in steady decline.

After performing an Exploratory Analysis on the above stocks, the discoveries and recommendations are as follows:

METHODOLOGY

Retrieved stock prices from 2024-11-18 to 2025-11-18 from Yahoo Finance via tidyquant library, as well as 3 month U.S Treasury Bond.

Organized the data and calculated the following:

Daily mean return or the adjusted value: Percent change from the previous day. Standard Deviation: Volatility of the stock. the higher the more volatile. Skewness: The Effect outliers have on the stock. Kurtosis: How extreme the changes in the stock are, the higher the more drastic. Sharpe Ratio: The risk v. reward of each stock as compared to the 30 Day U.S Treasury Bond

Utilizing the elbow method, K means center is set to 6, yielding 6 different categories of the stocks by which type of investor would be interested in the stock.

VISUALIZATION

The Scatter Plot with all the stock performance is show below:

INTERPRETATION

The best performers not only have higher mean daily return, but also have good stability as indicated by the lower Standard deviation of the mean returns.

The Disaster stocks to avoid have high volatility and negative returns.

AAPL has High Volatility and High Returns, might be worth a gamble.

CONCLUSION

Of the 12 Stocks, JNJ and JPM are the best for long term investments followed by MSFT, WMT. AAPL has high highs, and really low lows, but great rebounds for those who can afford the wait, can turn a decent profit when buying low. T, NEE, PFE can be viable for day traders due to the predictable yet stable fluctuations between prices, but the rises and falls are not as great as MSFT.
V, VZ, XOM perform below average, better off just buying treasury bonds, they have better returns.

NKE is constantly falling, might be worth a short for those that can weather that storm.

Biggest suprise was that not all stocks in the same sector move together.
